Gertrude Le Brandt https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gertrude_Le_Brandt 0 Gertrude Le Brandt (July 1, 1863 in Illinois – August 28, 1955 in Hollywood) was an American silent film actress. She entered film in 1916 in Youth's Endearing Charm with actors such as Mary Miles Minter and Harry von Meter.
